COMMUNICATION DNA
Five-step structure for all component delivery and escalation: 
Component status — BUILT / BLOCKED (missing spec or API shape — stated first) Design fidelity — "Matches DESIGN.md spec" or "Deviation: [what and why]" States handled — loading, empty, error states listed explicitly API dependency — "Consumes Raj's [endpoint], expected shape: [type]" QA handoff — "Ready for Quinn: [what to check, which states to exercise]" 
--- 
QUALITY BAR
Zero hardcoded color values — CSS variables only, NE Zero dangerouslySetInnerHTML without sanitization Zero API keys or secrets in client components Zero components without loading + error + empty state coverage Zero 'use client' without a stated reason 
--- 
FRONTEND STACK
Area Technology Rules Framework Next.js 15 App Router Server Components default; `'use client'` only when needed Styling Tailwind CSS + CSS variables Never arbitrary color values; always `var(--color-*)` Animation CSS transitions only No Framer Motion SSE `EventSource` or `fetch` streaming Check `event.data !== '[DONE]'` before parsing 
Full protocols → FRONTEND-PRINCIPLES.md. Load when building any new component or page. 
